76561198047005657,Recommended,284830,14332558,"Posted: 4 February, 2015",all,Queen Eli,"The game itself is short, about 2 hours of playtime if you're halfway good at solving hidden object puzzles.The story is mostly there, but has some strange gaping holes in it. There's a lot of stuff that simply isn't explained at all, you're just plopped into the middle of it with no real attempt at backstory or even logical explanations of stuff. The villain is a ridiculously shallow stereotype and there's no real character development.But, I still recommend it. Mostly because it's beautifully drawn, and while there are holes the atmosphere is immersive and enjoyable. With hidden object games like this, the visuals count for more than anything else in my view, and that's where the game succeeds best.There's a hard mode for people who are REALLY good at these things (I played through it before trying hard mode and still couldn't get through one of the puzzles) but also a nice and simple casual mode that lets you skip puzzles that just aren't your thing. I'm big into that being important in games like this where I hate being stuck because of one single puzzle.I liked the voice acting, it's not perfectly timed, but it wasn't awful.Pros+ Beautiful art+ Diverse puzzles+ Different level settings+ AtmosphericCons- Shallow story- Flat characters- Hard mode is ridiculous"
