,Recommended,284830,12921261,"Posted: 13 November, 2014",all,foxyshadis,"Quite an excellent Hidden Object/Adventure hybrid, with very well-done graphics (including all of the HO scenes), a plot seemingly straight out of a Jules Verne book, solid item puzzles and mini-games that mostly aren't too easy or difficult (although a some are obvious rehashes of common cliches), pretty good voice acting that covers nearly all conversation, and suitable music. Best of all, care was taken so that HO scenes reflect your last search the next time you need them; it's a personal pet peeve when they're just randomly generated every time. It's quite hard to see how it's related to the terrible ""Lost Civilization"" by the same company.Definitely recommended to HO lovers and Adventure puzzlers looking for a casual evening."
