,Recommended,284830,31287930,Posted: 21 April,all,Lunairetic,"This is my first puzzle game from Artifex Mundi, & I really enjoyed it!! Clockwork Tales is a point-and-click puzzle game with a steam punk theme. The art is very beautiful, & there are lots of very fun puzzles. Only 2 of the puzzles were any challenge at all however, so if you are looking for brain-benders then you will be disappointed. The steampunk theme works great for this puzzle game, & because of this most of the puzzles felt very natural in their placement rather than shoe-horned in. There's a good balance of Hidden Object Puzzles along with the other puzzles.The music is also beautiful, but there are only 3 tracks and it gets VERY repetitive. The game wasn't really long enough for the repetitiveness to get on my nerves however, & the puzzle music track in particular is very pretty! The voice work was also very good.The only thing that was a disappointment really was the story. It is a fairly simple, linear plot with no character development. There was just enough of a story to connect the puzzles & I just didn't care about Glass or Ink at all really, so it's a good thing that the puzzles were so fun!Completing the Prologue and the main story took me 6.6 hours, but I wasn't in any rush & took my sweet time so you could probably run through it much faster if you actually focused lol. I bought this on sale at some point but I don't emember what I paid. Definitely was worth the buy for me though.I recommend this game for someone who likes fun, creative, casual puzzle games, appreciates lovely artwork, & digs the steampunk aesthetic. Since there are no adult themes or language, & the story is simple, with the puzzles being not too challenging, I would also recommend this game for kids. :)"
