,Recommended,284830,33448219,Posted: 10 July,all,osirish,"Clockwork Tales: Of Glass and Ink is an extremely well crafted Hidden Object adventure set in a steampunk world, featuring beautiful graphics, a good soundtrack and strong voice acting. It comes with a bonus chapter that serves as a prequel to the main story.You play an investigator trying to get to the bottom of a mysterious series of earthquakes with a side-plot of rescuing your mentor along the way. The features a variety of puzzles and the HO scenes alternate between the usual finding objects based on a list and finding objects based on their outlines.About the only negative I had, and it's a small one, is that the puzzles although varied, were a little on the easy side.At 3 1/2 hours to beat including the bonus chapter, if you are a fan of the HO genre, you won't be disappointed."
